title: Baghdadi raid in Syria: Video released by Defense Department
text:
The Defense Department released video Wednesday of the U.S.-led weekend operation in northwestern Syria in which Islamic State leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi was killed and offered more insight into the raid.

What's new: U.S. Marine Corps Gen. Kenneth McKenzie, commander of U.S. Central Command, told reporters during a briefing that five other fighters from the Islamic State, or ISIS, also died during the operation, along with two children who were blown up by Bagdadhi when he detonated his suicide vest.

Go deeper: Baghdadi raid depended on international ties Trump has spurned

Editor's note: This is a developing news story. Please check back for updates.
description: Baghdadi detonated a suicide vest as U.S.-led forces closed in.
